sonusNodeResourcesMIB.name: sonusNodeResourcesMIB
sonusNodeResourcesMIB.contactinfo: Customer Support Sonus Networks, Inc, 5 carlisle Road Westford, MA 01886 USA Tel: 978-692-8999 Fax: 978-392-9118 E-mail: cs.snmp@sonusnet.com
sonusNodeResourcesMIB.description: The MIB Module for Node Resources Management.

sonusServProfileNextIndex.name: sonusServProfileNextIndex
sonusServProfileNextIndex.description: This field is deprecated. The next valid index to use when creating an entry in the sonusServProfileTable.

sonusServProfileTable.name: sonusServProfileTable
sonusServProfileTable.description: This field is deprecated. This table specifies the service profile list for the node.

sonusServProfileIndex.name: sonusServProfileIndex
sonusServProfileIndex.description: This field is deprecated. Identifies the target service profile entry.

sonusServProfileState.name: sonusServProfileState
sonusServProfileState.description: This field is deprecated. The administrative state of this service profile entry.

sonusServProfileName.name: sonusServProfileName
sonusServProfileName.description: This field is deprecated. The user name of this service profile.

sonusServProfileType.name: sonusServProfileType
sonusServProfileType.description: This field is deprecated. The type of endpoint (circuit or packet) supported by this service profile. Circuit endpoints support all the VCkt and VPkt profile parameters for echo cancellation and packetization. Packet endpoints support only the VPkt parameters for packetization.

sonusServProfileVCktEncoding.name: sonusServProfileVCktEncoding
sonusServProfileVCktEncoding.description: This field is deprecated. The audio encoding method to be performed on the voice data received from, and destined to the PSTN. The default encoding method is G.711 Ulaw.

sonusServProfileVCktBandwidth.name: sonusServProfileVCktBandwidth
sonusServProfileVCktBandwidth.description: This field is deprecated. The number of DS0 channels to group for Nx64 connections. Valid entries are 1 to 24 channels, allowing up to a complete set of T1 channels to be grouped at a single connection. The default bandwidth is 1 channel.

sonusServProfileVCktNecEnable.name: sonusServProfileVCktNecEnable
sonusServProfileVCktNecEnable.description: This field is deprecated. Specifies whether Network Echo Cancellation (NEC) is enabled for the channel. When enabled, NEC is enabled acording to the appropriate NEC configuration parameters. When disabled, the Voice Packet Assembler/Disassember (VPAD) operates in a circuit emulation mode.

sonusServProfileVPktEncoding.name: sonusServProfileVPktEncoding
sonusServProfileVPktEncoding.description: This field is deprecated. The audio encoding method to be performed on the packet data received from, and destined to the IP network. The default encoding method is G.711 Ulaw.

sonusServProfileVPktFrameSize.name: sonusServProfileVPktFrameSize
sonusServProfileVPktFrameSize.description: This field is deprecated. Specifies the number of samples per frame. For G.711 encoding mode, value must be a multiple of 8 samples. For G.723 encoding mode, value must be a multiple of 240 samples. For G.729A, value must be a multiple of 80 samples. Note that 8 samples represent one millisecond of voice data. A value of 0 specifies a frame size equal to the minimum for the encoding method (e.g 8 samples for G.711)

sonusServProfileVPktFramesPerPacket.name: sonusServProfileVPktFramesPerPacket
sonusServProfileVPktFramesPerPacket.description: This field is deprecated. Specifies the number of frames to transmit per packet. For G.711 encoding mode, valid values range from 5 to 40 frames, in increments of 5 frames. The default value for G.711 is 10 frames per packet. For G.723 encoding mode, valid values are 1 or 2, with a default value of 1 frame per packet. A value of 0 specifies the number of frames per packet equal to the default value for the encoding mode (e.g. 10 frames per packet for G.711).

sonusServProfileVPktMaxNetworkJitter.name: sonusServProfileVPktMaxNetworkJitter
sonusServProfileVPktMaxNetworkJitter.description: This field is deprecated. Specifies the maximum expected network jitter across the IP network in increments of 125usec. This value defines the size of the initial playout buffer required to absorb the maximum expected packet delay across the network. The minimum value is 40 (5msec) and the maximum value is 400 (50msec), with a default value of 80 (10msec).

sonusServProfileVPktTosValue.name: sonusServProfileVPktTosValue
sonusServProfileVPktTosValue.description: This field is deprecated. Specifies the Type Of Service (TOS) parameters to be provided in the IP header for voice packets. The TOS value is specified as an 8-bit hex value 0x00-0xFF allowing complete flexibility with respect to the contents of the TOS byte.

sonusServProfileCttTestType.name: sonusServProfileCttTestType
sonusServProfileCttTestType.description: This field is deprecated. For ISUP service profiles, specifies the type of continuity test to perform, based on the configuration of the remote switch or trunk connection. The remoteLoopback test is used when the remote switch will loop back channel being tested. The remote2Wire test is used when the remote switch supports the 2 wire continuity test procedure. And the remote4Wire test mode is used when the remote switch supports the 4 wire continuity test procedure. The default value is remoteLoopback.

sonusServProfileCttTimeout.name: sonusServProfileCttTimeout
sonusServProfileCttTimeout.description: This field is deprecated. For ISUP service profiles, specifies the overall test timeout value. The continuity test will be declared failed if the continuity tone is not detected within this timeout period. The timeout is specified in seconds, with a default value of 2 seconds.

sonusServProfileCttMinDetectTime.name: sonusServProfileCttMinDetectTime
sonusServProfileCttMinDetectTime.description: This field is deprecated. For ISUP service profiles, specifies the minimum time to detect the presence of the continuity test tone. The minimum detect time is specified in milliseconds, with a default time of 45 ms.

sonusServProfileCttMinReleaseTime.name: sonusServProfileCttMinReleaseTime
sonusServProfileCttMinReleaseTime.description: This field is deprecated. For ISUP service profiles, specifies the minimum time to detect that the continuity test tone has been removed and is no longer present. The minimum release time is specified in milliseconds, with a default time of 25 ms.

sonusServProfileCapability.name: sonusServProfileCapability
sonusServProfileCapability.description: This field is deprecated. Specifies the data capabilities for the circuit. This parameter specifies whether voice only, circuit mode data only, or both voice and circuit mode data can be supported by the circuit.

sonusServProfileDPktRestrictedCfg.name: sonusServProfileDPktRestrictedCfg
sonusServProfileDPktRestrictedCfg.description: This field is deprecated. Specifies whether the circuit may support 64 Kbit/s unrestricted data, or if the circuit supports 56 Kbit/s restricted data.

sonusServProfileDPktRtpPayloadType.name: sonusServProfileDPktRtpPayloadType
sonusServProfileDPktRtpPayloadType.description: This field is deprecated. Specifies the RTP payload type to be included in the RTP header of the voice data packet

sonusServProfileDPktMaxNetworkJitter.name: sonusServProfileDPktMaxNetworkJitter
sonusServProfileDPktMaxNetworkJitter.description: This field is deprecated. Specifies the maximum expected network jitter across the network for data calls in increments of 125usec. This value defines the size of the initial playout buffer required to absorb the maximum expected packet delay across the network. A separate value for data calls is provided to allow a single service profile to specify the jitter buffer size for both voice calls and data calls. The minimum value is 40 (5msec) and the maximum value is 400 (50msec), with a default value of 400 (50msec).

sonusSonicBusStatTable.name: sonusSonicBusStatTable
sonusSonicBusStatTable.description: This table presents Sonic Bus statistics for the node.

sonusSonicBusStatNumCalls.name: sonusSonicBusStatNumCalls
sonusSonicBusStatNumCalls.description: Indicates the number of active calls on the shelf.

sonusSonicBusStatBwAllocated.name: sonusSonicBusStatBwAllocated
sonusSonicBusStatBwAllocated.description: Indicates the percentage of Sonic Bus bandwidth allocated to the active calls on the shelf.

sonusSonicBusStatSduCount.name: sonusSonicBusStatSduCount
sonusSonicBusStatSduCount.description: Indicates the number of Sonic Bus data units allocated to the active calls on the shelf.

sonusActiveCallTable.name: sonusActiveCallTable
sonusActiveCallTable.description: This table presents the active call data for the node.

sonusActiveCallId.name: sonusActiveCallId
sonusActiveCallId.description: Represents the global call identifier (GCID) for the call. GCID is unique across the entire node.

sonusActiveCallSonicBusUnitsAllocated.name: sonusActiveCallSonicBusUnitsAllocated
sonusActiveCallSonicBusUnitsAllocated.description: Represents the SonicBus bandwidth allocated for the call expressed as SonicData Units per second.

sonusActiveCallNumResources.name: sonusActiveCallNumResources
sonusActiveCallNumResources.description: Represents the number of resources currently allocated to the call.

sonusActiveCallIngressServProfile.name: sonusActiveCallIngressServProfile
sonusActiveCallIngressServProfile.description: The name of the ingress service profile associated with this call.

sonusActiveCallEgressServProfile.name: sonusActiveCallEgressServProfile
sonusActiveCallEgressServProfile.description: The name of the egress service profile associated with this call.

sonusActiveCallCallingNum.name: sonusActiveCallCallingNum
sonusActiveCallCallingNum.description: The E.164 number representing the Calling Party's telephone number.

sonusActiveCallCalledNum.name: sonusActiveCallCalledNum
sonusActiveCallCalledNum.description: The E.164 number representing the Called Party's telephone number.

sonusActiveCallAddressTransPerformed.name: sonusActiveCallAddressTransPerformed
sonusActiveCallAddressTransPerformed.description: Indicates whether any address translation has been performed on the called party number. Valid translations are Local Number Portability (LPN), and 800 number translation (Tollfree).

sonusActiveCallOrigCalledNum.name: sonusActiveCallOrigCalledNum
sonusActiveCallOrigCalledNum.description: If an address translation has been performed on the called party number, this entry contains the original, untranslated number.

sonusActiveCallScenarioType.name: sonusActiveCallScenarioType
sonusActiveCallScenarioType.description: Specifies the call scenario type for this call.

sonusActiveCallIngressPstnSlotNum.name: sonusActiveCallIngressPstnSlotNum
sonusActiveCallIngressPstnSlotNum.description: For calls originating from the PSTN (circuit) side, indicates the slot of the circuit card on which the call was delivered.

sonusActiveCallIngressPstnPortNum.name: sonusActiveCallIngressPstnPortNum
sonusActiveCallIngressPstnPortNum.description: For calls originating from the PSTN (circuit) side, indicates the T1 port on the circuit card on which the call was delivered. For CNS10 cards, the port number will be in the range 1-12; for CNS30 cards, the port number will be in the range 1-28.

sonusActiveCallIngressPstnChannelNum.name: sonusActiveCallIngressPstnChannelNum
sonusActiveCallIngressPstnChannelNum.description: For calls originating from the PSTN (circuit) side, indicates the DS0 channel on which the call is being carried.

sonusActiveCallIngressPstnChannelCount.name: sonusActiveCallIngressPstnChannelCount
sonusActiveCallIngressPstnChannelCount.description: For calls originating from the PSTN (circuit) side, indicates the number of DS0 channels on which the call is being carried. This value is meaningful for Nx64 service calls.

sonusActiveCallIngressPstnChannelBitMap.name: sonusActiveCallIngressPstnChannelBitMap
sonusActiveCallIngressPstnChannelBitMap.description: For calls originating from the PSTN (circuit) side, provides a bit map of DS0 channels on which the call is being carried. For Nx64 service calls where N is greater than 1, multiple bits will be marked in the bit map.

sonusActiveCallEgressPstnSlotNum.name: sonusActiveCallEgressPstnSlotNum
sonusActiveCallEgressPstnSlotNum.description: For calls delivered to the PSTN (circuit) side, indicates the slot of the circuit card on which the call was delivered.

sonusActiveCallEgressPstnPortNum.name: sonusActiveCallEgressPstnPortNum
sonusActiveCallEgressPstnPortNum.description: For calls delivered to the PSTN (circuit) side, indicates the T1 port on the circuit card on which the call was delivered. For CNS10 cards, the port number will be in the range 1-12; for CNS30 cards, the port number will be in the range 1-28.

sonusActiveCallEgressPstnChannelNum.name: sonusActiveCallEgressPstnChannelNum
sonusActiveCallEgressPstnChannelNum.description: For calls delivered to the PSTN (circuit) side, indicates the DS0 channel on which the call is being carried.

sonusActiveCallEgressPstnChannelCount.name: sonusActiveCallEgressPstnChannelCount
sonusActiveCallEgressPstnChannelCount.description: For calls delivered to the PSTN (circuit) side, indicates the number of DS0 channels on which the call is being carried. This value is meaningful for Nx64 service calls.

sonusActiveCallEgressPstnChannelBitMap.name: sonusActiveCallEgressPstnChannelBitMap
sonusActiveCallEgressPstnChannelBitMap.description: For calls delivered to the PSTN (circuit) side, provides a bit map of DS0 channels on which the call is being carried. For Nx64 service calls where N is greater than 1, multiple bits will be marked in the bit map.

sonusActiveCallIngressLocalIpSockAddr.name: sonusActiveCallIngressLocalIpSockAddr
sonusActiveCallIngressLocalIpSockAddr.description: For calls originated on the IP (packet) side, indicates the IP address of the incoming (ingress) local socket connection.

sonusActiveCallIngressRemoteIpSockAddr.name: sonusActiveCallIngressRemoteIpSockAddr
sonusActiveCallIngressRemoteIpSockAddr.description: For calls originated on the IP (packet) side, indicates the IP address of the incoming (ingress) remote socket connection.

sonusActiveCallEgressLocalIpSockAddr.name: sonusActiveCallEgressLocalIpSockAddr
sonusActiveCallEgressLocalIpSockAddr.description: For calls delivered to the IP (packet) side, indicates the IP address of the outgoing (egress) local socket connection.

sonusActiveCallEgressRemoteIpSockAddr.name: sonusActiveCallEgressRemoteIpSockAddr
sonusActiveCallEgressRemoteIpSockAddr.description: For calls delivered to the IP (packet) side, indicates the IP address of the outgoing (egress) remote socket connection.

sonusActiveCallIngressPstnTrunk.name: sonusActiveCallIngressPstnTrunk
sonusActiveCallIngressPstnTrunk.description: For calls originating from the PSTN (circuit) side, specifies the trunk group name to which the Ingress Pstn Channel belongs.

sonusActiveCallEgressPstnTrunk.name: sonusActiveCallEgressPstnTrunk
sonusActiveCallEgressPstnTrunk.description: For calls delivered to the PSTN (circuit) side, specifies the trunk group name to which the Egress Pstn Channel belongs.

sonusActiveCallIngressIpDestGwName.name: sonusActiveCallIngressIpDestGwName
sonusActiveCallIngressIpDestGwName.description: For calls originating from the IP (packet) side, specifies the name of the remote gateway on which the call originated.

sonusActiveCallEgressIpDestGwName.name: sonusActiveCallEgressIpDestGwName
sonusActiveCallEgressIpDestGwName.description: For calls delivered to the IP (packet) side, specifies the name of the remote gateway to which the call was delivered.

sonusActiveCallDuration.name: sonusActiveCallDuration
sonusActiveCallDuration.description: Indicates the duration in seconds for this call following answer.

sonusActiveCallIngressEpType.name: sonusActiveCallIngressEpType
sonusActiveCallIngressEpType.description: Indicates the end point type for the ingress end point.

sonusActiveCallEgressEpType.name: sonusActiveCallEgressEpType
sonusActiveCallEgressEpType.description: Indicates the end point type for the egress end point.

sonusActiveCallIngressSgType.name: sonusActiveCallIngressSgType
sonusActiveCallIngressSgType.description: Indicates the signaling type for the ingress end point.

sonusActiveCallEgressSgType.name: sonusActiveCallEgressSgType
sonusActiveCallEgressSgType.description: Indicates the signaling type for the egress end point.

sonusActiveCallPacketsSent.name: sonusActiveCallPacketsSent
sonusActiveCallPacketsSent.description: Indicates the number of RTP packets sent on this call.

sonusActiveCallPacketsReceived.name: sonusActiveCallPacketsReceived
sonusActiveCallPacketsReceived.description: Indicates the number of RTP packets received on this call.

sonusActiveCallOctetsSent.name: sonusActiveCallOctetsSent
sonusActiveCallOctetsSent.description: Indicates the number of RTP octets sent on this call.

sonusActiveCallOctetsReceived.name: sonusActiveCallOctetsReceived
sonusActiveCallOctetsReceived.description: Indicates the number of RTP octets received on this call.

sonusActiveCallPacketsLost.name: sonusActiveCallPacketsLost
sonusActiveCallPacketsLost.description: Indicates the number of RTP packets lost on this call.

sonusActiveCallPacketsDiscarded.name: sonusActiveCallPacketsDiscarded
sonusActiveCallPacketsDiscarded.description: Indicates the number of RTP packets discarded by the jitter buffer.

sonusActiveCallInterarrivalJitter.name: sonusActiveCallInterarrivalJitter
sonusActiveCallInterarrivalJitter.description: Indicates the interarrival packet jitter on this call.

sonusActiveCallPacketLatency.name: sonusActiveCallPacketLatency
sonusActiveCallPacketLatency.description: Indicates the latency experienced on this call.

sonusCallResTable.name: sonusCallResTable
sonusCallResTable.description: This table presents the call resource data for the node. Each active call contains a set of allocated resources. This table provides a brief description and the information required to access detailed information about each allocated resource.

sonusCallResShelfIndex.name: sonusCallResShelfIndex
sonusCallResShelfIndex.description: Identifies the target shelf containing the call to be accessed.

sonusCallResSlotIndex.name: sonusCallResSlotIndex
sonusCallResSlotIndex.description: Identifies the target slot containing the call to be accessed.

sonusCallResCallIndex.name: sonusCallResCallIndex
sonusCallResCallIndex.description: Identifies the target call to be accessed.

sonusCallResIndex.name: sonusCallResIndex
sonusCallResIndex.description: Identifies the target resource index to access within the call.

sonusCallResId.name: sonusCallResId
sonusCallResId.description: Represents the internal resource identifier that uniquely represents the resource to the resource manager entity responsible for the resource.

sonusCallResCallId.name: sonusCallResCallId
sonusCallResCallId.description: Represents the global call identifier (GCID) for the call to which this resource is allocated. This information is provided to ensure that the resource is truly allocated to the call.

sonusCallResType.name: sonusCallResType
sonusCallResType.description: Specifies the resource type for this resource.

sonusCallResMgrHandle.name: sonusCallResMgrHandle
sonusCallResMgrHandle.description: Specifies the internal handle for the resource manager entity responsible for this resource. This element is provided for information only.

sonusCallResMgrShelfIndex.name: sonusCallResMgrShelfIndex
sonusCallResMgrShelfIndex.description: Specifies the shelf on which this resource resides.

sonusCallResMgrSlotIndex.name: sonusCallResMgrSlotIndex
sonusCallResMgrSlotIndex.description: Specifies the card slot on which this resource resides.

sonusCallPegCountsTable.name: sonusCallPegCountsTable
sonusCallPegCountsTable.description: This table presents call peg count statistics for the node.

sonusCallPegCountsShelfIndex.name: sonusCallPegCountsShelfIndex
sonusCallPegCountsShelfIndex.description: Identifies the target shelf to obtain the call counters.

sonusCallPegCountsReset.name: sonusCallPegCountsReset
sonusCallPegCountsReset.description: Provides a means to reset the active call attempt and completion counters. Any set operation on this object will result in the attempt and completion counters being cleared.

sonusCallPegCountsAttempts.name: sonusCallPegCountsAttempts
sonusCallPegCountsAttempts.description: Indicates the number of call attempts on this shelf.

sonusCallPegCountsCompletions.name: sonusCallPegCountsCompletions
sonusCallPegCountsCompletions.description: Indicates the total number of completed call attempts on this shelf.

sonusCallPegCountsActiveCalls.name: sonusCallPegCountsActiveCalls
sonusCallPegCountsActiveCalls.description: Indicates the current number of active calls in the shelf.

sonusCallPegCountsStableCalls.name: sonusCallPegCountsStableCalls
sonusCallPegCountsStableCalls.description: Indicates the current number of stable calls in the shelf.

sonusCallPegCountsUpdates.name: sonusCallPegCountsUpdates
sonusCallPegCountsUpdates.description: Indicates the number of call updates (modifications) on this shelf.

sonusCallPegCountsActiveCallsNonUser.name: sonusCallPegCountsActiveCallsNonUser
sonusCallPegCountsActiveCallsNonUser.description: Indicates the current number of active non-call associated signalling channels in the shelf. (ie ISDN D channel)

sonusCallPegCountsStableCallsNonUser.name: sonusCallPegCountsStableCallsNonUser
sonusCallPegCountsStableCallsNonUser.description: Indicates the current number of stable non-call associated signalling channels in the shelf. (ie ISDN D channel)

sonusToneProfileNextIndex.name: sonusToneProfileNextIndex
sonusToneProfileNextIndex.description: The next valid index to use when creating an entry in the sonusToneProfileTable.

sonusToneProfileTable.name: sonusToneProfileTable
sonusToneProfileTable.description: This table contains tone profiles for the node.

sonusToneProfileName.name: sonusToneProfileName
sonusToneProfileName.description: The user name of this tone profile.

sonusToneProfileGenerationMethod.name: sonusToneProfileGenerationMethod
sonusToneProfileGenerationMethod.description: Determines the generation method for the tone. This value is specified at object creation time and cannot be modified.

sonusToneProfileTone1Freq.name: sonusToneProfileTone1Freq
sonusToneProfileTone1Freq.description: Specifies Tone 1 Frequency in Hertz. If 0, then silence is generated. Only valid if generation method is singleTone or dualTone.

sonusToneProfileTone1Power.name: sonusToneProfileTone1Power
sonusToneProfileTone1Power.description: Specifies Tone 1 Power in dBm. Power levels range from -50 dBm (minimum power) to +3 dBm (maximum power). Only valid if generation method is singleTone or dualTone.

sonusToneProfileTone2Freq.name: sonusToneProfileTone2Freq
sonusToneProfileTone2Freq.description: Specifies Tone 2 Frequency in Hertz. If 0, then a single frequency tone is generated. Only valid if generation method is dualTone.

sonusToneProfileTone2Power.name: sonusToneProfileTone2Power
sonusToneProfileTone2Power.description: Specifies Tone 2 Power in dBm. Power levels range from -50 dBm (minimum power) to +3 dBm (maximum power). Only valid if generation method is dualTone.

sonusToneProfileCarrierFreq.name: sonusToneProfileCarrierFreq
sonusToneProfileCarrierFreq.description: Specifies the frequency in Hertz of the carrier for the modulated signal. Value must be less than 4000. If set to 0, then silence is generated. Only valid if generation method is modulatedTone.

sonusToneProfileSignalFreq.name: sonusToneProfileSignalFreq
sonusToneProfileSignalFreq.description: Specifies the frequency in Hertz of the sinusoid modulating the carrier sinusoid. Value must be less than 4000. Only valid if generation method is modulatedTone.

sonusToneProfileModPower.name: sonusToneProfileModPower
sonusToneProfileModPower.description: Specifies Carrier Power in dBm. Power levels range from -50 dBm (minimum power) to +3 dBm (maximum power). Only valid if generation method is modulatedTone.

sonusToneProfileModIndex.name: sonusToneProfileModIndex
sonusToneProfileModIndex.description: Specifies the modulation index of the signal. Value must be in the range of 0 to 300 in 1% units. Only valid if generation method is modulatedTone.

sonusToneProfileMake1.name: sonusToneProfileMake1
sonusToneProfileMake1.description: Duration of the first on cadence in milliseconds. If 0, then the duration of the first on cadence is 0 msec. If -1, then the tone is played continuously.

sonusToneProfileBreak1.name: sonusToneProfileBreak1
sonusToneProfileBreak1.description: Duration of the first off cadence in milliseconds. If 0, then silence is not generated between the on cadences. If -1, then silence is generated continuously.

sonusToneProfileMake2.name: sonusToneProfileMake2
sonusToneProfileMake2.description: Duration of the second on cadence in milliseconds. If 0, then the duration of the second on cadence is 0 msec. If -1, then the tone is played continuously.

sonusToneProfileBreak2.name: sonusToneProfileBreak2
sonusToneProfileBreak2.description: Duration of the second off cadence in milliseconds. If 0, then silence is not generated between the on cadences. If -1, then silence is generated continuously.

sonusToneProfileMake3.name: sonusToneProfileMake3
sonusToneProfileMake3.description: Duration of the thrid on cadence in milliseconds. If 0, then the duration of the third on cadence is 0 msec. If -1, then the tone is played continuously.

sonusToneProfileBreak3.name: sonusToneProfileBreak3
sonusToneProfileBreak3.description: Duration of the third off cadence in milliseconds. If 0, then silence is not generated after the third on cadence. If -1, then silence is generated continuously.

sonusToneProfileRepeat.name: sonusToneProfileRepeat
sonusToneProfileRepeat.description: Number of cadence cycles to generate. If 0, then the tone pattern is repeated indefinitely.

sonusToneTypeNextIndex.name: sonusToneTypeNextIndex
sonusToneTypeNextIndex.description: The next valid index to use when creating an entry in the sonusToneTypeTable.

sonusToneTypeTable.name: sonusToneTypeTable
sonusToneTypeTable.description: This table contains tone types for the node.

sonusToneTypeName.name: sonusToneTypeName
sonusToneTypeName.description: The user name of this tone type. Possible types include 'dial', 'busy', 'reorder', etc.

sonusTonePackageNextIndex.name: sonusTonePackageNextIndex
sonusTonePackageNextIndex.description: The next valid index to use when creating an entry in the sonusTonePackageTable.

sonusTonePackageTable.name: sonusTonePackageTable
sonusTonePackageTable.description: This table contains tone packages for the node.

sonusTonePackageName.name: sonusTonePackageName
sonusTonePackageName.description: The name of this tone package. This name should reflect the country or carrier which will be using this package.

sonusTonePkgElemTable.name: sonusTonePkgElemTable
sonusTonePkgElemTable.description: This table contains elements which bind tone types to tone profiles for a given tone package.

sonusTonePkgElemIndex.name: sonusTonePkgElemIndex
sonusTonePkgElemIndex.description: Identifies the target tone package element.

sonusTonePkgElemTonePackageRef.name: sonusTonePkgElemTonePackageRef
sonusTonePkgElemTonePackageRef.description: Identifies the tone packge for this element.

sonusTonePkgElemToneTypeRef.name: sonusTonePkgElemToneTypeRef
sonusTonePkgElemToneTypeRef.description: Identifies the tone type for this element.

sonusTonePkgElemToneProfileRef.name: sonusTonePkgElemToneProfileRef
sonusTonePkgElemToneProfileRef.description: The name of the tone profile that this tone type maps to for this tone package.

sonusDigitProfileNextIndex.name: sonusDigitProfileNextIndex
sonusDigitProfileNextIndex.description: The next valid index to use when creating an entry in the sonusDigitProfileTable.

sonusDigitProfileTable.name: sonusDigitProfileTable
sonusDigitProfileTable.description: This table contains digit profiles for the node. Digit Profiles contain both digit generation (sonusDigitProfileGen...) and digit detection (sonusDigitProfileDet...) parameters.

sonusDigitProfileName.name: sonusDigitProfileName
sonusDigitProfileName.description: The user name of this digit profile.

sonusDigitProfileType.name: sonusDigitProfileType
sonusDigitProfileType.description: Specifies the digit's format. This value is set at object creation time and cannot be modified.

sonusDigitProfileGenPower.name: sonusDigitProfileGenPower
sonusDigitProfileGenPower.description: Specifies digit generation power level in dBm. Power level ranges from -50 dBm (minimum power) to +3 dBm (maximum power).

sonusDigitProfileGenMake.name: sonusDigitProfileGenMake
sonusDigitProfileGenMake.description: Specifies duration of generated digits in milliseconds.

sonusDigitProfileGenBreak.name: sonusDigitProfileGenBreak
sonusDigitProfileGenBreak.description: Specifies silence between generated digits in milliseconds.

sonusDigitProfileDetMinPower.name: sonusDigitProfileDetMinPower
sonusDigitProfileDetMinPower.description: Specifies minimum power level in dBm required for digit detection. Valid levels range from -45dBm to -25dBm.

sonusDigitProfileDetMinOnDuration.name: sonusDigitProfileDetMinOnDuration
sonusDigitProfileDetMinOnDuration.description: Specifies minimum tone duration in milliseconds required for digit detection. The value must in increments of 5ms. For DTMF digits, the value must be between 25ms and 80ms. For MF digits, the value must be between 25ms and 100ms.

sonusDigitProfileDetMinOffDuration.name: sonusDigitProfileDetMinOffDuration
sonusDigitProfileDetMinOffDuration.description: Specifies minimum interdigit duration in milliseconds for digit detection. The value must be in increments of 5ms. For DTMF digits, the value must be between 25ms and 80ms. For MF digits, the value must be between 10ms and 100ms.

sonusDigitProfileDetFreqAcceptRange.name: sonusDigitProfileDetFreqAcceptRange
sonusDigitProfileDetFreqAcceptRange.description: Specifies frequency tolerances for digit detection. For DTMF digits the value represents accept and reject ranges. For MF digits the value represents only the accept range. Frequencies detected within the accept range will result in digit detection. Frequencies detected outside the reject range will not result in digit detection. . DTMF DTMF MFR1 VALUE ENUMERATION ACCEPT REJECT ACCEPT ----- ----------- ---------------- ------------------ 1 narrow +/-2.0% +/-3.0% +/-(1.5% + 5Hz) 2 medium +/-2.5% +/-3.5% +/-(1.5% + 10Hz) 3 wide +/-3.0% +/-4.0% +/-(1.5% + 15Hz) 4 wider +/-3.5% +/-4.5% N/A

sonusDigitProfileDtmfDetTwistCutoff.name: sonusDigitProfileDtmfDetTwistCutoff
sonusDigitProfileDtmfDetTwistCutoff.description: For DTMF digit detection only. Twist is the ratio of high group power to low. Twist ratios below the twist cutoff will result in digit detection. Twist ratios above the twist cutoff will result in digit rejection. Value must be between 4dB and 12dB in increments of 2dB.

sonusDigitProfileMfr1GenMakeKp.name: sonusDigitProfileMfr1GenMakeKp
sonusDigitProfileMfr1GenMakeKp.description: Specifies duration of generated KP digit in milliseconds. Only applicable if digit type is MFR1.

sonusCktServProfileTable.description: This table specifies the Circuit service profile list for the node.

sonusCktServProfileIndex.description: Identifies the target circuit service profile entry.

sonusCktServProfileState.description: The administrative state of this circuit service profile entry.

sonusCktServProfileName.description: The name of this circuit service profile.

sonusCktServProfileAudioEncoding.name: sonusCktServProfileAudioEncoding
sonusCktServProfileAudioEncoding.description: The audio encoding method to be performed on the voice data received from, and destined to the PSTN. The default encoding method is G.711 Ulaw.

sonusCktServProfileBandwidth.name: sonusCktServProfileBandwidth
sonusCktServProfileBandwidth.description: The number of DS0 channels to group for Nx64 connections. Valid entries are 1 to 24 channels, allowing up to a complete set of T1 channels to be grouped at a single connection. The default bandwidth is 1 channel.

sonusCktServProfileNecEnable.name: sonusCktServProfileNecEnable
sonusCktServProfileNecEnable.description: Specifies whether Network Echo Cancellation (NEC) is enabled for the channel. When enabled, NEC is enabled acording to the appropriate NEC configuration parameters. When disabled, the echo chaceller is bypassed.

sonusCktServProfileCttTestType.name: sonusCktServProfileCttTestType
sonusCktServProfileCttTestType.description: For ISUP service profiles, specifies the type of continuity test to perform, based on the configuration of the remote switch or trunk connection. The remoteLoopback test is used when the remote switch will loop back channel being tested. The remote2Wire test is used when the remote switch supports the 2 wire continuity test procedure. And the remote4Wire test mode is used when the remote switch supports the 4 wire continuity test procedure. The default value is remoteLoopback.

sonusCktServProfileCttTimeout.name: sonusCktServProfileCttTimeout
sonusCktServProfileCttTimeout.description: For ISUP service profiles, specifies the overall test timeout value. The continuity test will be declared failed if the continuity tone is not detected within this timeout period. The timeout is specified in seconds, with a default value of 2 seconds.

sonusCktServProfileCttMinDetectTime.name: sonusCktServProfileCttMinDetectTime
sonusCktServProfileCttMinDetectTime.description: For ISUP service profiles, specifies the minimum time to detect the presence of the continuity test tone. The minimum detect time is specified in milliseconds, with a default time of 45 ms.

sonusCktServProfileCttMinReleaseTime.name: sonusCktServProfileCttMinReleaseTime
sonusCktServProfileCttMinReleaseTime.description: For ISUP service profiles, specifies the minimum time to detect that the continuity test tone has been removed and is no longer present. The minimum release time is specified in milliseconds, with a default time of 25 ms.

sonusCktServProfileCapability.name: sonusCktServProfileCapability
sonusCktServProfileCapability.description: Specifies the data capabilities for the circuit. This parameter specifies whether voice only, circuit mode data only, or both voice and circuit mode data can be supported by the circuit.

sonusCktServProfileDataRestrictedCfg.name: sonusCktServProfileDataRestrictedCfg
sonusCktServProfileDataRestrictedCfg.description: Specifies whether the circuit may support 64 Kbit/s unrestricted data, or if the circuit supports 56 Kbit/s restricted data.

sonusCktServProfileDtmfProfileName.name: sonusCktServProfileDtmfProfileName
sonusCktServProfileDtmfProfileName.description: The name of DTMF profile associated with this circuit service profile.

sonusCktServProfileInterworkingXfrCap.name: sonusCktServProfileInterworkingXfrCap
sonusCktServProfileInterworkingXfrCap.description: The transfer capability for audio calls when interworking with CAS. The default transfer capability is speech.

sonusPktServProfileNextIndex.name: sonusPktServProfileNextIndex
sonusPktServProfileNextIndex.description: The next valid index to use when creating an entry in the sonusPktServProfileTable.

sonusPktServProfileTable.description: This table specifies the packet service profile list for the node.

sonusPktServProfileIndex.description: Identifies the target packet service profile entry.

sonusPktServProfileState.name: sonusPktServProfileState
sonusPktServProfileState.description: The administrative state of this packet service profile entry.

sonusPktServProfileName.name: sonusPktServProfileName
sonusPktServProfileName.description: The user name of this packet service profile.

sonusPktServProfileDestProtocol.name: sonusPktServProfileDestProtocol
sonusPktServProfileDestProtocol.description: Specifies the Packet Destination Protocal used. GSX - uses Sonus GSX-GSX MCS protocol. h323 - uses H.323 protocol.

sonusPktServProfilePrfdAudioEncoding.name: sonusPktServProfilePrfdAudioEncoding
sonusPktServProfilePrfdAudioEncoding.description: The preferred audio encoding method to be performed on the packet data received from, and destined to the IP network. The possible options are: G.711, G.711 with Silence Suppression, G.729A and G.729A+B. The default encoding method is G.711. For G.711, the law is determined by Circuit Service Profile.

sonusPktServProfilePrfdFramesPerPacket.name: sonusPktServProfilePrfdFramesPerPacket
sonusPktServProfilePrfdFramesPerPacket.description: Specifies the Preferred Audio Encoding Packet Size in milliseconds. For G.711 encoding mode, valid values range from 10 ms to 40 ms, in increments of 5 ms. The default value for G.711 is 10 ms. For G.729 encoding mode, valid values from 10 ms to 40 ms, in increments of 10 ms. The default value for G.729 is 20 ms.

sonusPktServProfileDefFramesPerPacket.name: sonusPktServProfileDefFramesPerPacket
sonusPktServProfileDefFramesPerPacket.description: Specifies the default Audio Encoding Packet Size in milliseconds. For G.711 encoding mode, valid values range from 10 ms to 40 ms, in increments of 5 ms. The default value for G.711 is 10 ms. For G.729 encoding mode, valid values from 10 ms to 40 ms, in increments of 10 ms. The default value for G.729 is 20 ms.

sonusPktServProfileDefAudioEnable.name: sonusPktServProfileDefAudioEnable
sonusPktServProfileDefAudioEnable.description: Specifies whether or not to allow default Audio (G.711). If enabled, allow use of G.711 if preferred audio resource is not available. If disabled, Do not use of G.711 if preferred audio resource is not available and the call is disconnected.

sonusPktServProfileSilenceFactor.name: sonusPktServProfileSilenceFactor
sonusPktServProfileSilenceFactor.description: Specifies percentage of call time that silence is expected.

sonusPktServProfileVInitPlayoutBufDelay.name: sonusPktServProfileVInitPlayoutBufDelay
sonusPktServProfileVInitPlayoutBufDelay.description: This value defines the size of the initial playout bufferrequired to absorb the maximum expected voice packet delay across the network. Range from 1 ms to 50 ms, in increments of 1 ms.

sonusPktServProfileFaxRelay.name: sonusPktServProfileFaxRelay
sonusPktServProfileFaxRelay.description: If never is specified, Fax Relay is not used regardless of the audio encoding method. If useIfCompressedAudio is specified, Fax Relay is used if the compressed resource is available. If always is specified, Fax Relay is used regardless of the audio encoding method.

sonusPktServProfileDtmfRelay.name: sonusPktServProfileDtmfRelay
sonusPktServProfileDtmfRelay.description: If never is specified, DTMF Relay is not used regardless of the audio encoding method. If useIfCompressedAudio is specified, DTMF Relay is used if the compressed resource is available. If always is specified, DTMF Relay is used regardless of the audio encoding method.

sonusPktServProfileFallbackHandling.name: sonusPktServProfileFallbackHandling
sonusPktServProfileFallbackHandling.description: This specifies the behavior when a compressed codec call needs to revert to G.711 (e.g., to pass modem data) and there is no bandwidth available.

sonusPktServProfileTosValue.name: sonusPktServProfileTosValue
sonusPktServProfileTosValue.description: Specifies the Type Of Service (TOS) parameters to be provided in the IP header for voice packets. The TOS value is specified as an 8-bit hex value 0x00-0xFF allowing complete flexibility with respect to the contents of the TOS byte.

sonusPktServProfileDInitPlayoutBufDelay.name: sonusPktServProfileDInitPlayoutBufDelay
sonusPktServProfileDInitPlayoutBufDelay.description: This value defines the size of the initial playout buffer required to absorb the maximum expected data packet delay across the network. Range from 5 ms to 50 ms, in increments of 1 ms. The default value is 50 ms.

sonusPktServProfileDataRtpPayloadType.name: sonusPktServProfileDataRtpPayloadType
sonusPktServProfileDataRtpPayloadType.description: Specifies the RTP payload type to be included in the RTP header of the data packet

sonusPktServProfileG711SendSidPackets.name: sonusPktServProfileG711SendSidPackets
sonusPktServProfileG711SendSidPackets.description: Specifies whether sending SID packets is enabled. This applies only if preferred audio encoding is G.711 with silence suppression.

sonusPktServProfileG711SidRtpPayloadType.name: sonusPktServProfileG711SidRtpPayloadType
sonusPktServProfileG711SidRtpPayloadType.description: Specifies G.711 SID RTP payload type. This applies only if preferred audio encoding is G.711 with silence suppression. Range 0 to 127.

sonusPktServProfileSidHeartbeat.name: sonusPktServProfileSidHeartbeat
sonusPktServProfileSidHeartbeat.description: Specifies whether sending SID heartbeat packets is enabled. This applies if preferred audio encoding is either G.711 with silence suppression or G.729A+B.

sonusPktServProfileRtcp.name: sonusPktServProfileRtcp
sonusPktServProfileRtcp.description: Specifies whether RTCP is enabled for the call.

sonusPktServProfilePacketLossThreshold.name: sonusPktServProfilePacketLossThreshold
sonusPktServProfilePacketLossThreshold.description: Specifies the RTCP packet loss threshold in packets/100,000. 0 means no detection. Requires RTCP to be enabled.

sonusPktServProfilePacketLossAction.name: sonusPktServProfilePacketLossAction
sonusPktServProfilePacketLossAction.description: Specifies the action taken when the packet loss threshold is exceeded. Requires RTCP to be enabled.

sonusPktServProfileRtpPeerAbsenceAction.name: sonusPktServProfileRtpPeerAbsenceAction
sonusPktServProfileRtpPeerAbsenceAction.description: Specifies the action taken when the RTP peer is detected to be absent (due to lack of RTP and RTCP packets). Requires RTCP to be enabled.

sonusPktServProfileDtmfRelayOutOfBand.name: sonusPktServProfileDtmfRelayOutOfBand
sonusPktServProfileDtmfRelayOutOfBand.description: Specifies whether out of band DTMF relay is enabled. This applies if DTMF relay is configured as useIfCompressedAudio or always .

sonusPktServProfileDtmfRelayRemoveDigits.name: sonusPktServProfileDtmfRelayRemoveDigits
sonusPktServProfileDtmfRelayRemoveDigits.description: Specifies whether removing DTMF digits from the media stream is enabled. This applies if DTMF relay is configured as useIfCompressedAudio or always .

sonusNodeResourcesCallAdmissionSuspended.description: This trap indicates that call admission into the GSX has been suspended. Information provided by this trap includes the reason why call admission has been suspended.
